**Markdown to HTML Conversion Function**
=====================================

Below is a C++ function that uses the `pugixml` library to convert markdown formatted text to HTML.

### Prerequisites

*   Install the `pugixml` library by running `sudo apt-get install libpugixml-dev` (for Ubuntu-based systems) or by following the installation instructions on the [pugixml GitHub page](https://github.com/zeux/pugixml).

### Code

```cpp
#include <pugixml.hpp>
#include <string>

/**
 * Converts markdown formatted text to HTML.
 *
 * @param markdownText The markdown formatted text to convert.
 * @return The HTML formatted text.
 */
std::string markdownToHtml(const std::string& markdownText) {
    pugi::xml_document doc;
    pugi::xml_parse_result result = doc.load_string(markdownText.c_str());

    if (!result) {
        // Handle parsing errors
        return "";
    }

    pugi::xml_node root = doc.document_element();
    std::string htmlText;

    // Convert markdown to HTML
    for (pugi::xml_node node = root.first_child(); node; node = node.next_sibling()) {
        if (node.type() == pugi::node_element) {
            pugi::xml_node child = node.first_child();
            while (child) {
                if (child.type() == pugi::node_text) {
                    // Convert markdown text to HTML
                    std::string text = child.value();
                    // Replace markdown syntax with HTML
                    text = pugixml::escape(text);
                    htmlText += text;
                }
                child = child.next_sibling();
            }
        }
    }

    return htmlText;
}
```

### Example Usage

```cpp
int main() {
    std::string markdownText = "# Heading\n## Subheading\nThis is a paragraph.";
    std::string htmlText = markdownToHtml(markdownText);
    std::cout << htmlText << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

This code defines a function `markdownToHtml` that takes a markdown formatted string and returns the equivalent HTML formatted string. The function uses the `pugixml` library to parse the markdown text and convert it to HTML.

**Note**: This code assumes that the markdown text is well-formed and does not contain any syntax errors. You may need to add error handling to suit your specific requirements.

