### Step 1: Include the `tocloft` Package

First, you need to include the `tocloft` package in your document preamble. This package provides a simple way to customize the table of contents.

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{tocloft}
```

### Step 2: Use the `\tableofcontents` Command

Next, use the `\tableofcontents` command in your document body, typically after the `\begin{document}` command.

```latex
\begin{document}
\tableofcontents
```

### Step 3: Add Chapters and Sections

To generate a table of contents, you need to add chapters and sections to your document. Use the `\chapter` and `\section` commands for this purpose.

```latex
\chapter{Chapter 1}
\section{Section 1.1}
\section{Section 1.2}

\chapter{Chapter 2}
\section{Section 2.1}
\section{Section 2.2}
```

### Step 4: Compile the Document

Finally, compile your LaTeX document to generate the table of contents.

### Example Document

